[thinking] **Evaluating dynamic loading risks**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering the rules that allow catching errors for dynamic loading, but our pre-generated class might create a risk due to its static initialization in OJDBC. I wonder if relying solely on metadata updates is sufficient. Alternatively, I could create custom simple classes and manually provide the generated proxy in my test source. This approach would give me full control without needing extra metadata, while still using Class.forName for the dynamic proxy class.
[thinking] 
