"text\":\"**Inspecting constructor requirements**\\n\\nI need to look into the class constructor for SampleService, which takes parameters like Object, ProxyFactory, Map, and a boolean. I notice it doesn't need generated method bodies, except possibly for _Proxy_. I wonder if ProxyFactory.extractDelegate is utilizing methods from the _Proxy_ interface. I should definitely take some time to inspect the _Proxy_ to clarify how it all fits together.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_hrZPRKTrHQBMBXf9SoLm5ATJ|fc_09a2af978a4013a50169f7c9a167dc819da5b83638d73900b5", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "JAR=/home/vjovanov/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.oracle.database.jdbc/ojdbc11/23.8.0.25.04/4d80d6fb56bbb5e20b3e3fa3183f2af13b533515/ojdbc11-23.8.0.25.04.jar; javap -classpath \"$JAR\" -p oracle.jdbc.proxy._Proxy_", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2154, "output": 1400, "cacheRead": 86528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 90082, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777846666712, "responseId": "resp_09a2af978a4013a50169f7c98b4fdc819d9b866d4c162ba6a6"}}
